20 PART V. SBI AUTHORITY FOR CRIMINAL HISTORY CHECKS
21 SECTION 5. G.S. 143B-1209.11 reads as rewritten:
22 "§ 143B-1209.11. Criminal record checks of school personnel.
23 (a) The State Bureau of Investigation may provide a criminal record check to the local
24 board of education governing body of a public school unit of a person who is employed in a
25 public school in that local school district that public school unit or of a person who has applied
26 for employment in a public school in that local school district, that public school unit, if the
27 employee or applicant consents to the record check. The Bureau may also provide a criminal
28 record check of school personnel as defined in G.S. 115C-332 G.S. 115C-77 by fingerprint card
29 to the local board of education governing body of the public school unit from National
30 Repositories of Criminal Histories, in accordance with G.S. 115C-332. G.S. 115C-77. The
31 information shall be kept confidential by the local board of education governing body of the
32 public school unit as provided in G.S. 115C-77 and Article 21A of Chapter 115C of the General
33 Statutes.
34 (a1) The State Bureau of Investigation may provide a criminal record check to the State
35 Board of Education of an applicant for licensure under Article 17E of Chapter 115C of the
36 General Statutes, if the applicant consents to the record check. The Bureau may also provide a
37 criminal record check of an applicant, as defined in G.S. 115C-270.1(1a) by fingerprint card to
38 the State Board of Education from the National Repositories of Criminal Histories, in accordance
39 with G.S. 115C-270.12. The information shall be kept confidential by the State Board of
40 Education as provided in G.S. 115C-270.12(e).
41 (a2) The State Bureau of Investigation may provide a criminal record check to the Charter
42 Schools Review Board of a member of a board of directors of a nonprofit seeking initial approval
43 to establish a charter school under Article 14A of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes, if the
44 member consents to the record check. The Bureau may also provide a criminal record check of a
45 member, as defined in G.S. 115C-218.4(a)(2), by fingerprint card to the Charter Schools Review
46 Board from the National Repositories of Criminal Histories, in accordance with
47 G.S. 115C-218.4. The information shall be kept confidential by the Charter Schools Review
48 Board as provided in G.S. 115C-218.4(e).
49 (a3) The State Bureau of Investigation may charge a fee to offset the cost incurred by it to
50 conduct a criminal record check under subsections (a1) and (a2) of this section. The fee shall not
51 exceed the actual cost of locating, editing, researching, and retrieving the information.
